  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the safety and efficacy of targeted cryoablation
      therapy for hepatic carcinoma.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A cryoprobe is inserted percutaneously under CT guidance into the targeted lesion. Patients
      undergo ablation using a freeze-thaw-freeze cycle lasting approximately 10-6-10minutes.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
